<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/446:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="to">Gilbert</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-03T16:00:00-05:00">January 3, 1933—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1. For <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Reber</persName>. Your telegram
                                349, December 31, 11 a.m. from London. You may use your discretion
                                as to whether or not it would be useful to discuss the situation
                                with League and/or Committee officials, or furnish them with copies
                                of the “law” and <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Mitchell</persName>’s
                                letter to <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Barclay</persName>.</p>
                            <p>On December 30 <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Mitchell</persName>
                                reported the receipt of a “note from Executive Mansion signed by
                                    <persName corresp="#p_J1">Johnson</persName> one of <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Barclay</persName>’s secretaries” which was
                                offensive in tone and endeavored to take issue with the statements
                                contained in <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Mitchell</persName>’s
                                letter. <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Mitchell</persName> has been
                                instructed to have the clerk of the Legation return the
                                communication and to inform the sender that the “American Minister
                                declines to accept a communication of this nature.”</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>